<refentry id="psmstart">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>psmstart</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>psmstart</refname>
    <refpurpose>
      start a program on a remote node using the ParaStation daemon <xref
	linkend="psid"/>
    </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>psmstart</command>
      <arg choice="plain">program</arg>
      <arg rep="repeat">arg</arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      Start <command>program</command> on a remote node using the
      ParaStation daemon <xref linkend="psid"/>. All arguments given at the
      command line will be passed to the remotely started
      <command>program</command>.
    </para>
    <para>
      All output of <command>program</command> will be forwarded completely
      to the local terminal. All input <command>program</command> is
      expecting will be redirected from the local terminal. If the remote
      program catches a signal, a message will be printed.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Implementation</title>
    <para>
      If <command>psmstart</command> is called, <command>program</command>
      is started remotely using the ParaStation daemon <xref
	linkend="psid"/>. Within the startup the local process will become a
      IO handling process forwarding all the input and output
      data. Suspending the local process or sending a signal to this local
      process will <emphasis>not</emphasis> affect the remotely started
      process.
    </para>
  </refsect1>


  <refsect1>
    <title>Limitations</title>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  The suspending of remotely started processes is not possible.
	</para> 
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Signals sent to the local process will <emphasis>not</emphasis> be
	  forwarded correctly to the remote process.
	</para> 
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  The return value of <command>program</command> will not be forwarded
	  correctly to the controlling shell. 
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>See also</title>
    <para>
      <xref linkend="psid"/>, <xref linkend="spawning"/>
    </para>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>
